Habit of thinking by letters
>The power to "consciously cut and connect" the "link" between the "abstract" [symbol] of "word" and the "concrete" [sense] of "feeling" is necessary. However, in the history of mankind, "the cost of reproduction of letters has decreased while the cost of reproduction of figures has remained high" due to "letterpress printing". This led to the de facto adoption of an "expressive form" that "communicates mainly by writing. As a result, the habit of thinking mainly through letters has developed.

